-- SKS Microfinance Gets Bids for All Shares Offered in Initial Public Sale
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-07-30T06:02:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/sks-microfinance-gets-bids-for-all-shares-offered-in-initial-public-sale.html

          
          
             SKS Microfinance Ltd., the Indian
lender backed by investors including George Soros, received bids
for all the stock available in its intial public offering as it
seeks to raise as much as $347 million.  
 The company got 14.4 million bids for the 13.8 million
shares on offer, according to data on the National Stock
Exchangeâ€™s website today. The offer of shares for 850 rupees to
985 rupees apiece ends today for institutional buyers. The sale
closes for retail investors on Aug 2.  
